IZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Harl</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2:06:24 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">*Querry*</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have some questions to set before all of you. <br>
  1. Where can I find the cheepest largest mana stones?<br>
     Brocolli Tom has shown me a nice place just between Lin and Nanto that I can get the 50mana ones at for just under 400p. I would like to know where I can get 250s to 500s the cheepest.<br>
  2. Come next lvl I will be able to spens 6 skill points. Lockpick and healing are unusable and missle def is untrained. With Missle def I will be able to wear some of the better armors but with lockpick...Well<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Also healing would be wonderful in the citadel as the luggies drop hordes of kits but I currently I have a Life magicIII orb. Will I need healing later and would it be late enough that I can ad up the points to get it as a trained skill in time.<br>
 So many decisions not enough time<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Whatever shall I do? Please feel free to poast any advice you can give me.         Haggriden Lusarl.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:30:20 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hmmmm ...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">If I were you I would take healing. Others might not agree but let me explain why. A Life Orb is great...but it takes mana to heal. Healing kits are easy to come by and pretty fast to use in battle. Unlike your orb where you have to unequip your sword and then equip the orb. The downside to kits are that if you are below 50% of your normal health the kits will fail at times. The more below that 50% mark..the greater percent chance that your heal will fail. I've seen some use a life I wand to get to 50% then a kit for the rest. Plus, look at a healing kit as free mana! Cast health to mana to get mana and then use a kit to heal. Rinse and repeat amd you will be casting tons of buffs. As for missile def ... Crow has it but not up to a point where he can wear any great armor with missile d requirements. Syndra does not have it and can take skellies and lugians pretty well so far. However, she is not yet in the citidal with multiple rock chuckers throwing boulders her way. I might regret not having it then. Locky pick ... ask Dia and Roy. My 2 pyreals.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:49:47 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Hmmmm ...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">My opinion would be to take healing also. I use healing all the time for mana renewal, it's nice! When I am in the citadel, I keep multiple stamina elix's and at least 3 health elix's in my hotkeys. If you take a pretty thorough beating you can pop a health elix and then heal up from there in no time at all. I keep a healing kit in slot 8 and my backpack in slot 9--fast and easy.<br>
<br>
I decided a long time ago to try Roy without missile D. I instead put points into melee D and try to find really good armor, hehe. I take a few small hits in the citadel, but never enough that I can't outlast a gigas rock supply. When we were in the sclava cathedral, I would have had a problem if I had been alone. Having multiple lvl 20+ archers constantly flinging arrows is a bit much.<br>
<br>
Lockpick is a skill that I have used very little overall, but when you need it, YOU NEED IT. There is nothing like having a great, ravenous army storming across a battlefield and get to the castle door....and they can't get in, LOL. However, in hindsight, I would trade lockpick for those skill points toward Life magic now. Ghar says-- &quot;Hang in there Roy, I just looked, you can take Life Magic at level 70!&quot;</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9:39:50 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=3><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Healing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I couldn't live without healing. I even heal in the middle of a battle. I try not to fall under 65% health. I take one step back to get out of battle, press &quot;8&quot;&quot;9&quot; (my healing kit and backpack are in hotkeys just like Roy said) and I'm back at 100%. Or in Olthoi nest, tanking 3 Olthois, I kill one, heal, number 2, heal, and number 3, heal, loot, voila!<br>
<br>
Where do you get your healing elexir Roy? I never seem to have enough of those. When my health drops under 25%, it's no use trying to heal with 2 or 3 baddies on my tail. Quick an elexir and a heal and watch out!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>ezOP</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>11:10:42 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=4><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Healing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I buy them in Zhaik. They are by no means the cheapest I have seen, but they are handy as I buy my mana stones there as well. 980p per 100 mana (also not the cheapest but convenient--I think the stones in Zhaik rank at about the 4th cheapest in the game)</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10/28/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2:33:29 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=5><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Healing</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Another vote here for healing!!! Now that you're in the Citadel and facing waves of bad guys, you have to heal in the middle of a fight, and the only way to do it is with healing kits and potions. The advantage of kits is they're lighter, cheaper, and most importantly, with a high healing skill and an excellent kit, you can recover much more health from a single heal than you can from gulping a potion. As Crow said, the downside is it's unreliable. One rule of thumb is to try to keep your healing skill at least 20 points higher than your health, and always heal before you drop below half health. If you drop below that, gulp some potions then switch to a kit.<br>
<br>
And health-to-mana is a godsend while buffing! I always keep a peerless kit in hotkey 1, my backpack in 2, and a good kit in 3. I use the peerless in combat, and the good kit to heal between fights or while buffing. The good kit is also a backup in case the peerless runs out in battle. Stamina elixers and healing potions (for when you drop below half-health) also get hot-keyed.<br>
<br>
As far as prices, the best place for mana charges I've found on a major portal loop is Zaikhal. If you want to travel a bit, you can get better prices in Eastham or the Tired Mage outside of Mayoi (not the mage in town). For healing supplies, I still haven't found a cheaper place than Qalaba'r. But you shouldn't need to buy any healing kits; the Citadels are Dereth's equivalent of a free clinic! Just pick them up off the Lugies, they're very considerate that way!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR></TABLE><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=95%><TR><TD ALIGN=LEFT></TD><TD ALIGN=RIGHT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showMessage?topicID=300.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1><< Prev Topic</FONT></A> &nbsp;<A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showMessage?topicID=294.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Next Topic >></FONT></A> </TD></TR></TABLE><BR><TABLE WIDTH=95% BORDER=0><TR><TD><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=295.topic&index=5><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/addReply1.gif border=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=295.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/images/email.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Email This To a Friend"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;Email This To a Friend</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.threadControl?topicID=295.topic><IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/deleteThreadFire.gif BORDER=0 ALT="Topic Control Image"></A><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Topic Commands (Moderator only)</FONT><BR><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=295.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Subscribe</FONT></A>  <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Click to receive email notification of replies</FONT><BR><A HREF=http